# App Architecture & Technical Specifications
## Early Emotional Distress Detection & Support App

---

## 1. System Architecture Overview

### 1.1 High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Mobile App<br/>iOS & Android] --> B[API Gateway]
    B --> C[Application Server]
    C --> D[Authentication Service]
    C --> E[Data Processing Service]
    C --> F[AI/ML Service]
    C --> G[Notification Service]
    C --> H[Moderation Service]
    
    E --> I[(User Database)]
    E --> J[(Analytics Database)]
    F --> K[AI Model Storage]
    H --> L[Content Moderation Queue]
    
    C --> M[External Integrations]
    M --> N[Crisis Helplines API]
    M --> O[Therapist Directory API]
    M --> P[SMS/Email Service]
    
    I --> Q[Backup & Recovery]
    J --> Q
```

### 1.2 Architecture Principles

1. **Privacy First:** End-to-end encryption, local-first data storage
2. **Offline Capable:** Core features work without internet
3. **Scalable:** Microservices architecture for independent scaling
4. **Reliable:** 99.9% uptime for crisis features
5. **Secure:** HIPAA-compliant data handling (if applicable)

---

## 2. Technology Stack Recommendations

### 2.1 Mobile Application

**Framework:** React Native or Flutter

**Rationale:**
- Cross-platform (iOS + Android) from single codebase
- Native performance
- Large community and libraries
- Cost-effective development

**Alternative:** Native development (Swift for iOS, Kotlin for Android) if budget allows

**Key Libraries:**
- **Local Storage:** SQLite with SQLCipher (encryption)
- **State Management:** Redux or MobX
- **Notifications:** Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)
- **Analytics:** Firebase Analytics (privacy-compliant)
- **Offline Sync:** WatermelonDB or Realm

### 2.2 Backend Services

**Language:** Node.js (Express) or Python (FastAPI)

**Rationale:**
- Fast development
- Excellent for real-time features (AI chat)
- Strong ecosystem for AI/ML integration

**API Architecture:** RESTful API + WebSocket for real-time chat

**Authentication:** JWT (JSON Web Tokens) with refresh tokens

### 2.3 Database

**Primary Database:** PostgreSQL

**Rationale:**
- Robust, ACID-compliant
- Excellent for structured data (mood logs, assessments)
- Strong encryption support
- JSON support for flexible data

**Caching Layer:** Redis

**Rationale:**
- Fast session management
- Real-time features (chat, notifications)
- Rate limiting for API protection

**Analytics Database:** MongoDB or BigQuery

**Rationale:**
- Flexible schema for analytics
- Time-series data optimization
- Aggregation capabilities

### 2.4 AI/ML Services

**AI Chat:** OpenAI GPT-4 API or Google Gemini API

**Rationale:**
- State-of-the-art natural language understanding
- Empathetic response generation
- Fine-tunable for mental health context

**Crisis Detection:** Custom ML model (BERT-based)

**Training Data:**
- Annotated mental health crisis text
- Suicide prevention datasets (ethically sourced)

**Deployment:** TensorFlow Serving or AWS SageMaker

### 2.5 Cloud Infrastructure

**Recommended:** AWS, Google Cloud, or Azure

**Services:**
- **Compute:** AWS EC2 / Google Compute Engine (auto-scaling)
- **Storage:** AWS S3 / Google Cloud Storage (encrypted)
- **CDN:** CloudFront / Cloud CDN (fast global access)
- **Monitoring:** CloudWatch / Stackdriver
- **Security:** AWS WAF / Google Cloud Armor

**Alternative for Budget:** DigitalOcean or Heroku (early stage)

### 2.6 Third-Party Integrations

| Service | Purpose | Provider Options |
|---------|---------|------------------|
| **SMS/Email** | Notifications, OTP | Twilio, SendGrid |
| **Push Notifications** | App notifications | Firebase Cloud Messaging |
| **Analytics** | User behavior (privacy-compliant) | Mixpanel, Amplitude |
| **Error Tracking** | Bug monitoring | Sentry, Rollbar |
| **Payment** | Premium features (if any) | Stripe, Razorpay |

---

## 3. Data Architecture

### 3.1 Data Models

