## 4. Privacy & Security Architecture

### 4.1 Data Encryption

**At Rest:**
- Database: AES-256 encryption
- File storage: Server-side encryption (SSE)
- Sensitive fields (notes, journals): Additional field-level encryption

**In Transit:**
- TLS 1.3 for all API communications
- Certificate pinning in mobile app

**On Device:**
- SQLCipher for local database
- iOS Keychain / Android Keystore for credentials

### 4.2 Authentication & Authorization

**Authentication Flow:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[User Opens App] --> B{First Time?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Create Account]
    B -->|No| D[Login]
    
    C --> E[Generate Anonymous ID]
    E --> F[Create Encryption Keys]
    F --> G[Store Keys Securely]
    G --> H[Issue JWT Token]
    
    D --> I[Verify Credentials]
    I --> J{Valid?}
    J -->|Yes| H
    J -->|No| K[Reject]
    
    H --> L[Access Token + Refresh Token]
    L --> M[Authenticated Session]
```

**Authorization:**
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- User can only access own data
- Moderators can access flagged content only
- Admins have audit-only access (no PII)

### 4.3 Privacy Compliance

**GDPR Compliance (if applicable):**
- ✅ Right to access: Users can export all data
- ✅ Right to deletion: Users can delete account and all data
- ✅ Data minimization: Collect only necessary data
- ✅ Consent: Clear opt-in for data collection
- ✅ Data portability: JSON export of user data

**HIPAA Compliance (if applicable in US):**
- ✅ Encrypted storage and transmission
- ✅ Access controls and audit logs
- ✅ Business Associate Agreements (BAA) with vendors
- ✅ Breach notification procedures

**India-Specific:**
- Compliance with Digital Personal Data Protection Act (DPDP)
- Data localization (store Indian user data in India)

### 4.4 Anonymization for Analytics

**Process:**
```mermaid
graph LR
    A[User Data] --> B[Remove PII]
    B --> C[Hash User IDs]
    C --> D[Aggregate Metrics]
    D --> E[Analytics Database]
    E --> F[Insights Dashboard]
```

**Anonymized Metrics:**
- Aggregate mood trends (no individual identification)
- Feature usage statistics
- Crisis event frequency (no user details)
- Retention and engagement rates

---

## 5. AI/ML Architecture

### 5.1 AI Chat System

**Architecture:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[User Message] --> B[Input Validation]
    B --> C[Crisis Keyword Detection]
    C -->|Crisis| D[Immediate Crisis Response]
    C -->|Normal| E[Context Retrieval]
    
    E --> F[Recent Chat History]
    F --> G[User Mood Context]
    G --> H[AI Model GPT-4/Gemini]
    
    H --> I[Response Generation]
    I --> J[Safety Filter]
    J -->|Safe| K[Return Response]
    J -->|Unsafe| L[Fallback Response]
    
    D --> M[Emergency Resources]
    K --> N[Log Interaction]
    L --> N
```

**Prompt Engineering:**

System Prompt:
```
You are a compassionate mental health support companion. Your role is to:
1. Listen without judgment
2. Validate emotions
3. Suggest coping techniques when appropriate
4. NEVER diagnose or provide medical advice
5. Detect crisis situations and escalate immediately

User context:
- Primary stressors: {workload, family}
- Recent mood: {sad, stress level 4/5}
- Crisis history: {none}

Respond with empathy and support.
```

### 5.2 Crisis Detection Model

**Model:** Fine-tuned BERT for text classification

**Training:**
- Dataset: Annotated mental health crisis text
- Labels: [crisis, high_risk, medium_risk, low_risk]
- Accuracy target: 95%+ for crisis detection

**Deployment:**
- Real-time inference (<500ms)
- Fallback to keyword matching if model unavailable

**Continuous Improvement:**
- Human-in-the-loop: Moderators review false positives/negatives
- Periodic retraining with new data

---

## 6. Integration Architecture

### 6.1 Crisis Helpline Integration

**Current:** Display phone numbers for manual calling

**Future Enhancement:** Direct API integration

**Potential Partners:**
- AASRA
- Vandrevala Foundation
- iCall

**Integration Flow:**
```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Crisis Detected] --> B[User Taps Call]
    B --> C[App Initiates Call]
    C --> D[Helpline Receives Call]
    D --> E[Optional: Send Context]
    E --> F[Counselor Assists]
```

**Context Sharing (with user consent):**
- Recent mood trends
- Crisis trigger (if known)
- Safety plan (if created)

### 6.2 Therapist Directory Integration

**Purpose:** Help users find professional help

**Data Sources:**
- Psychology Today API
- Local mental health directories
- Verified therapist databases

**Features:**
- Filter by location, specialization, language
- Insurance compatibility
- Availability
- User reviews

---

## 7. Scalability Considerations

### 7.1 Horizontal Scaling

**Stateless Services:**
- API servers can scale horizontally
- Load balancer distributes traffic
- Auto-scaling based on CPU/memory usage

**Database Scaling:**
- Read replicas for analytics queries
- Sharding by user_id for large datasets
- Connection pooling

### 7.2 Performance Optimization

**Caching Strategy:**
- Redis for session data (TTL: 24 hours)
- CDN for static assets
- API response caching (short TTL for dynamic data)

**Database Optimization:**
- Indexes on frequently queried fields (user_id, timestamp)
- Partitioning for time-series data (mood logs by month)
- Query optimization and monitoring

### 7.3 Load Estimates

**Assumptions:**
- 100,000 active users
- 60% daily active users (DAU)
- Average 5 API calls per session

**Calculations:**
- Daily API calls: 100,000 × 0.6 × 5 = 300,000
- Peak load (assuming 20% in peak hour): 60,000 calls/hour = 16.7 calls/second

**Infrastructure:**
- 2-4 API servers (with auto-scaling)
- 1 primary database + 2 read replicas
- 1 Redis instance

---

## 8. Monitoring & Observability

### 8.1 Key Metrics

**Application Metrics:**
- API response time (target: <200ms)
- Error rate (target: <0.1%)
- Uptime (target: 99.9%)

**User Metrics:**
- Daily/Monthly Active Users (DAU/MAU)
- Feature usage rates
- Crisis event frequency

**Business Metrics:**
- User retention (7-day, 30-day)
- Engagement rate (check-ins completed)
- Professional help referrals

### 8.2 Alerting

**Critical Alerts:**
- API downtime
- Database connection failures
- Crisis detection model failures
- Spike in crisis events

**Warning Alerts:**
- High error rates
- Slow response times
- Low disk space

### 8.3 Logging

**Log Levels:**
- ERROR: System failures, exceptions
- WARN: Unusual patterns, deprecated features
- INFO: User actions (anonymized)
- DEBUG: Detailed troubleshooting (dev only)

**Log Retention:**
- 30 days for operational logs
- 90 days for audit logs
- Permanent for crisis events (anonymized)

---

## 9. Deployment Architecture

### 9.1 Environments

**Development:**
- Local development environment
- Shared dev database
- Mock external services

**Staging:**
- Production-like environment
- Anonymized production data (optional)
- Full integration testing

**Production:**
- Multi-region deployment (for redundancy)
- Blue-green deployment for zero-downtime updates
- Automated rollback on failures

### 9.2 CI/CD Pipeline

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Code Commit] --> B[Automated Tests]
    B --> C{Tests Pass?}
    C -->|Yes| D[Build Docker Image]
    C -->|No| E[Notify Developer]
    D --> F[Push to Registry]
    F --> G[Deploy to Staging]
    G --> H[Integration Tests]
    H --> I{Tests Pass?}
    I -->|Yes| J[Manual Approval]
    I -->|No| E
    J --> K[Deploy to Production]
    K --> L[Health Checks]
    L --> M{Healthy?}
    M -->|Yes| N[Complete]
    M -->|No| O[Rollback]
```

---

## 10. Disaster Recovery & Business Continuity

### 10.1 Backup Strategy

**Database Backups:**
- Automated daily backups
- Retention: 30 days
- Encrypted and stored in separate region

**Recovery Time Objective (RTO):** 4 hours
**Recovery Point Objective (RPO):** 24 hours

### 10.2 Failover Strategy

**Database:**
- Primary-replica setup
- Automatic failover to replica
- Manual promotion if needed

**Application Servers:**
- Multi-region deployment
- DNS failover to secondary region

---

## 11. Cost Estimation (Monthly)

**Assumptions:** 100,000 active users

| Component | Service | Estimated Cost |
|-----------|---------|----------------|
| **Compute** | AWS EC2 (4 instances) | $400 |
| **Database** | AWS RDS PostgreSQL | $300 |
| **Storage** | AWS S3 | $50 |
| **CDN** | CloudFront | $100 |
| **AI API** | OpenAI GPT-4 (100k calls) | $500 |
| **Notifications** | Firebase + Twilio | $200 |
| **Monitoring** | CloudWatch + Sentry | $100 |
| **Total** | | **$1,650/month** |

**Note:** Costs scale with user base. Optimize with reserved instances and volume discounts.

---

## 12. Technology Alternatives (Budget-Conscious)

### 12.1 Open-Source Alternatives

| Commercial | Open-Source Alternative |
|------------|-------------------------|
| OpenAI GPT-4 | Llama 3 (self-hosted) |
| AWS | DigitalOcean, Hetzner |
| Firebase | Supabase, Appwrite |
| Sentry | Self-hosted Sentry |

**Trade-offs:**
- Lower cost
- More maintenance overhead
- Potentially lower performance

---

## Conclusion

This architecture is designed to be:

✅ **Secure & Private:** End-to-end encryption, GDPR/HIPAA compliant  
✅ **Scalable:** Microservices, horizontal scaling  
✅ **Reliable:** 99.9% uptime, disaster recovery  
✅ **Cost-Effective:** Optimized for early-stage deployment  
✅ **Maintainable:** Modern tech stack, CI/CD automation  

The architecture prioritizes **user safety and privacy** while ensuring the app can scale to serve millions of users in need.

